@startuml Smart City Area

!include smart-city-topology.puml

' An administrative division, unit, entity, area or region,
' also referred to as a subnational entity, constituent unit, or country subdivision,
' is a portion of a country or other region delineated for the purpose of administration.
' (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Administrative_division)
entity AdministrativeArea <<abstract>> extends Feature {
}

' A district is a type of administrative division that, in some countries, is managed by local government.
' Across the world, areas known as 'districts' vary greatly in size, spanning regions
' or counties, several municipalities, subdivisions of municipalities, school district, or political district.
' (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/District)
'
' <<bridge>> decision:
' - **`District`** — the Smart City side of the District ↔ SubGeographicalRegion semantic gap. A District is a
'   civic/administrative zone defined by city governance, while SubGeographicalRegion is an electrical topology zone
'   defined by grid infrastructure. Both partition the same physical city space but use entirely different boundaries
'   and naming conventions. The agent must negotiate this mismatch — correlating a charging station's district
'   membership with the SubGeographicalRegion (and its Substation) that provides its electrical supply.
entity District <<bridge>> extends AdministrativeArea {
}

' A neighbourhood (British English), or neighborhood (American English; see spelling differences),
' is a geographically localised community within a larger city, town, suburb or rural area.
' (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neighbourhood)
'
' <<bridge>> decision:
' - **`Neighbourhood`** — finer-grained Smart City side of the same spatial gap as District. A Neighbourhood
'   represents a sub-district community zone (e.g., a downtown block cluster), which may map more precisely to a
'   single Substation service area than a full District does. When the agent resolves which transformer serves a
'   charging station, Neighbourhood provides a more granular named anchor than District, reducing the spatial
'   search to a smaller candidate set of UsagePoints and PowerTransformers.
entity Neighbourhood <<bridge>> extends AdministrativeArea {
}

@enduml